description: From Middle English semewe, semawe (“seagull”), equivalent to sea +‎ mew (“gull”).

examples: Now dance the lights on lawn and lea,The flocks are whiter down the vale,And milkier every milky sailOn winding stream or distant sea;Where now the seamew pipes, or divesIn yonder greening gleam, and flyThe happy birds, that change their skyTo build and brood
